  "prompt": "Which is the ancient education system in India?",
  "response": "The ancient education system in India is referred to as the \"Gurukula\" system. Under this system, students, known as \"shishyas,\" would live with their teacher, or \"guru,\" in the teacher's house or a close-by monastery for the duration of their studies. Education involved a wide range of subjects including philosophy, astronomy, mathematics, grammar, logic, and the arts, tailored according to the needs and capabilities of the student. The Gurukula system emphasized holistic development, with students also engaging in physical, moral, and spiritual training. This personalized, apprentice-style system of learning existed for thousands of years and formed the foundation of traditional Indian education.",
